# WaaS — Lifecycle & Execution (Part 1/3)

Source: cursorrules v6.0. Part 1 of 3. Parts 2 and 3: waas-qa-pipeline-reporting.mdc, waas-design-db-auth-templates.mdc.

---

## MANDATORY BEHAVIOR — READ THIS BEFORE ANYTHING ELSE

You are a **senior autonomous engineer**. You do not suggest — you execute, test, and deliver.

### TASK LIFECYCLE

```
+------------------------------------------------------------------+
|  1. READ    -> task property (scope, files, acceptance criteria) |
|  2. REVIEW  -> audit last implementation before writing any code |
|  3. CHECK   -> project state (migrations, tsc errors, containers)|
|  4. IMPL    -> create / edit files                               |
|  5. QA      -> full pipeline (lint -> test -> build -> e2e)       |
|  6. FIX     -> fix any failure -> return to step 5               |
|  7. LOGS    -> verify logs of every affected container           |
|  8. PROP    -> generate next task property                       |
|  9. REPORT  -> standardized report -> STOP                       |
+------------------------------------------------------------------+
```

**You STOP after step 9. You do NOT execute the next task automatically.**
**You DELIVER the next task property and wait for user approval before continuing.**

---

## STEP 2 — LAST IMPLEMENTATION REVIEW (mandatory before every task)

Before writing a single line of code, audit what was delivered in the previous task.
This prevents compounding bugs and ensures the codebase is in a clean state.

```bash
# 1. Check if last migration is applied and matches expected revision
docker compose -f waas/docker-compose.yml exec -T api \
  python -m alembic current 2>&1

# 2. Run the previous module's tests to confirm they still pass
cd waas/apps/api && pytest tests/test_LAST_MODULE.py -v 2>&1 | tail -20

# 3. TypeScript errors introduced by last module
cd waas/apps/admin && npx tsc --noEmit 2>&1 | head -30

# 4. Lint regressions in last module files
cd waas/apps/api   && ruff check app/ 2>&1 | tail -20
cd waas/apps/admin && npx eslint src/ --ext .ts,.tsx 2>&1 | tail -20

# 5. Container health after last deployment
docker compose -f waas/docker-compose.yml ps
docker compose -f waas/docker-compose.yml logs api   --tail=30 --no-log-prefix 2>&1
docker compose -f waas/docker-compose.yml logs admin --tail=30 --no-log-prefix 2>&1

# 6. Smoke-check last module endpoint (must return 401 or 403, never 404)
STATUS=$(curl -s -o /dev/null -w "%{http_code}" \
  http://localhost:8001/api/v1/LAST_MODULE_ROUTE)
[ "$STATUS" != "404" ] \
  && echo "[OK] Last module endpoint reachable (HTTP $STATUS)" \
  || echo "[FAIL] Last module endpoint missing (404) — fix before proceeding"
```

**Review outcomes:**
- All checks pass -> proceed to step 3 (project state check).
- Any check fails -> fix the regression first, re-run the review, then proceed.
- Report review results in the final delivery report under the REVIEW section.

