## IDE & EXTENSIONS (use when available)

**Python (Pylance + Ruff)** — The official Python extension with Pylance gives real-time FastAPI diagnostics. With the Ruff extension, errors appear underlined before running the pipeline. The agent can read diagnostics (e.g. via Read Lints) and fix issues before executing any command.

**Docker** — The official Microsoft Docker extension shows container status, logs, and health in the sidebar. The agent can inspect container state and logs from the IDE without running `docker compose logs` in the terminal when the extension is in use.

**Optional (not urgent):** SonarLint — real-time bug/vulnerability analysis; can be verbose for fast cycles. GitLens — useful to see changes between tasks; the last-implementation review step in the lifecycle already covers that flow.
